Lleyton Hewitt is still targeting sole ownership of the record title haul at the Queen's Club Aegon Championships after easing into the second round.

The 33-year-old Australian last won in Kensington in 2006 and shares the all-time record of four tournament victories with American Andy Roddick.

Hewitt reached the semi-finals last year, before being dislodged by Marian Cilic - and believes that run sparked a resurgence in form leading to him claiming the Brisbane International title.

