Hewitt is still ranked 43 in the world, but said he has no interest in the statistics - instead he will chase that elusive fifth Queen's title and a positive run at Wimbledon.

"I don't set any targets over that, I couldn't care less about my ranking," he said.

"Obviously I want to win every tournament I enter, and every match I play.

"The majors are still the top motivation, and in a couple of weeks' time it's one of the big ones for me."

